  "footnotes": [
    "Manchuria column represents the dominant power in Manchuria and Liaodong; Goguryeo and Balhae were Korean-lineage states that also controlled this zone",
    "Gojoseon (c. 2333–108 BCE) is the first recorded Korean state; the 'Jin state' refers to proto-Korean tribal confederacies south of the Han River",
    "Balhae (698–926) is considered a successor state to Goguryeo by Korean historiography; Chinese historiography treats it as a regional regime (Bohai)",
    "Jeju Island (Tamna) remained an independent polity until absorbed by Goryeo in 938 CE",
    "The Modern row shows occupation zones (1945–1948) stacked above the post-1948 division into DPRK and ROK"
  ]
